RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VERSATILE stalked the pace in the four path, bid at the eighth pole and drew off under little urging. CAMBIASO stalked the pace in the three path, bid at the half-mile mark, faltered in the stretch but held the place. GHOST BIKE was clear early in the two path, then couldn't hold off the closers. FLAT OUT FREDA stalked the pace in the two path, then had no late bid. OFFSHORE TITHE stalked the pace in the four path but faded in the stretch. STEALTH MISSION stalked the pace inside before fading at the half. TOTALITARIAN came in at the seven-eighths pole to squeeze a rival, rushed up and was steadied repeatedly down the backstretch, then gave way. LADYONTHEHILL was hopped and brushed at the start, then was squeezed back and checked on the first turn, trailed and was eased, then was walked home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: came in 7/8,squeezed foe,steadied down backstretch,,gave way 1/2

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NIGHTTIME JUSTICE chased the pace from the four path into the far turn, bid three wide in late turn to be a serious contender, took aim on the leader into the lane then wore that one down through the final seventy yards. LASHES pressed the pace two wide through the turn, bid into the lane , gained the lead when straightening, dueled with the winner through the final eighth and could not hold. SMOOTH JUSTICE was two wide and in the three path through the turn, came into the lane from the five path with aim on the top ones and could not sustain the bid. AZURITA was last away, lost her path and was steadied soon after the start, trailed through the turn and into the lane, shifted into the four path and offered a mild gain. MI ESTRELLA chased the pace along the inside through the turn then faded through the lane. KANFU set the pace from the two path into late turn then gave way. INCREDIBLE JUSTICE broke alertly then settled to the back after the first call and trailed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 36000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 12 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINGLE HER broke alertly to gain the lead at once, set the pace from the two path through the turn and into the backstretch, remained clear through the far turn and into the lane then widened to the wire while being kept to the task. EMERSON'S DREAM saved ground through the turns and into the lane then chased the winner through the final eighth while coming off the rail a couple paths. LITTLE GRAY FLOWER raced near the rail through the far turn, came into the lane under a drive from the two path, could not gain on the winner while making up some ground on the place rival. BIRDSOFAFEATHER raced along the rail through the far turn and into the lane and was never a serious threat. GOLDEN HEIST was in the three path when near the back, came into the lane five wide and moved up while in the seven path. SHARON'S GREY HOPE was in the four path through the turns, swung into the lane from the eight path and never menaced. EXPLOSIVE SKIES raced in the three path through the turns when never far back, came into the lane five wide and tired. PRETTY HEART chased the pace from the two path through the far turn then was empty through the lane. PADDI'S WISH chased the pace from the three path into the far turn and was done in late turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WE STORM was reserved through the turn when in the three path, came into the lane from the seven path when still well behind, asked for more inside the eighth pole and had another gear while quickly passing several and won going away. WASHINGTON'S UNION vied for the lead near the rail, cleared on the backstretch, was joined by another through the far turn, was no match for the winner but stayed on well through the final eighth from between rivals to inch back up for the place spot. STORMIN MIDNIGHT vied early then settled back to chase the pace through the turn, continued along the inside into the lane and just missed the place spot. QAADER was bumped at the start, raced along the inside through the turns when never far back, angled into the eight path for the drive and moved up late. THE MOTTO vied for the lead from the three path through the far turn while two wide, continued in the three or four path into the lane, gained the lead outside the eighth pole then faltered. PITAGORE chased the pace from the three path through the far turn, was well placed into the lane then weakened. FAITH RUNNER was in the four to the three path through the first turn, continued off the inside through the far turn and never factored. SIMPLY JACK was in the two or three path into the far turn, bid three wide in mid-turn and into the lane then tired. TAPTHEDRUM was four wide through the far turn, swung into the lane from off the rail, was in the nine path in mid-stretch and never factored. TROY BOY trailed throughout while along the inside.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Shelby County H. HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 80. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No nomination fee, $150 to pass the entry box and an additional $100 to start, with $100,000 Guaranteed. Supplementary nominations may be made by the usual time of closing of ent ries for a fee of $625 which will include entry and starting fees. After paying 1% to all owners of horses finishing sixth through last the purse will be divided, 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth and 3% to fifth. Weights: Wed nesday, May 31. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usual time of closing. Trophy to the winning owner. This race will be limited to 12 starters. If more than 12 horses pass the entry box preference will be given to those with the highest weights, with the scale of weights considered. Second preference will be highest lifetime earnings. Entry fee only will be refunded if failure to draw into the race. Nominations closed on Wednesday, May 24, 2023, with 14 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOTOX KATIE trailed at the first call while in the two path, moved to the three path through the turn, gained momentum in late turn, guided into the six path for the drive and rallied from mid-track to be clear at the wire. BELLA BOLLE stalked the pace from the three path into the turn, bid three wide in late turn, got clear with an eighth to go then could not hold off the winner while finishing clear for the place spot. LIL EVIE chased four wide through the turn, had aim on the leaders from mid-track then needed more late. COMPRESSED ENERGY saved ground through the turn when near the back, shifted into the three or four path and was gaining to the end. FOREVER NOTED vied for the lead two wide through the turn, continued a serious contender with an eighth left then gave way. EVERYTHING'S ROSY chased the pace from the two path into the turn, checked behind rivals, stayed on and never was a serious threat thereafter. EXPRESS LADY saved ground into the lane, moved up and was not a factor. NO TRUST never a factor while in the four path through the turn. BETCHA set the early pace before the first call, was joined by another into the turn, vied with that one into the lane then faded. HUNGARIAN PRINCESS bid five wide through late turn when appearing to loom a threat then was empty after turning into the lane. HOOSIER PREMIUM was done early while off the inside.
